name: FSourceControlState
doc:
Snapshot of source control state of a file
@see        USourceControlHelpers::QueryFileState()

Filename: Get the local filename that this state represents
bIsValid: Indicates whether this source control state has valid information (true) or not (false)
bIsUnknown: Determine if we know anything about the source control state of this file
bCanCheckIn: Determine if this file can be checked in.
bCanCheckOut: Determine if this file can be checked out
bIsCheckedOut: Determine if this file is checked out
bIsCurrent: Determine if this file is up-to-date with the version in source control
bIsSourceControlled: Determine if this file is under source control
bIsAdded:
Determine if this file is marked for add
@note        if already checked in then not considered mid add
bIsDeleted: Determine if this file is marked for delete
bIsIgnored: Determine if this file is ignored by source control
bCanEdit: Determine if source control allows this file to be edited
bCanDelete: Determine if source control allows this file to be deleted.
bIsModified: Determine if this file is modified compared to the version in source control.
bCanAdd:
Determine if this file can be added to source control (i.e. is part of the directory
structure currently under source control)
bIsConflicted: Determine if this file is in a conflicted state
bCanRevert: Determine if this file can be reverted, i.e. discard changes and the file will no longer be checked-out.
bIsCheckedOutOther: Determine if this file is checked out by someone else
CheckedOutOther: Get name of other user who this file already checked out or "" if no other user has it checked out
